<AbstractNarration>This workshop brings together researchers to discuss current topics and trends in quantum communications. This meeting addresses a central issue belonging to the NSF's Quantum Leap Big Idea, related to development of secure and scalable modes of communication based on quantum phenomena. Participants come from a diverse pool of convergent disciplines, ranging from chemistry, materials sciences, engineering to physics and quantum information. A post-meeting report is planned to summarize the current status and challenges in the field. Members of underrepresented groups and minorities will be encouraged to apply.</AbstractNarration>
